{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> λάβρος</b>, ον <br /> (also α, ον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Damocrates Poeta Medicus cited in 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 13.917)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] only of wind and water, <b>furious, boisterous</b>, Ζέφυρος λάβρος ἐπαιγίζων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.148, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 15.293, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Ventis” 50; ὡς ὅτε κῦμα θοῇ ἐν νηῒ πέσῃσι λάβρον 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.625; ποταμὸς.. λ. ὕπαιθα ῥέων 21.271; ὅτε λαβρότατον χέει ὕδωρ Ζεύς 16.385: λ. ὄμβρος 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.12 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; καπνός, σέλας, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 8.36, “P.” 3.40; πνεῦμα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 110 (Lyric poetry); πῦρ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 697 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λάβρον αὐχέν᾽, of the Hellespont personified, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Timotheus Lyricus “Persae” 84 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; simply, <b>huge, mighty</b>, λίθος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 8.46 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὕδατα λαβρότερα, explained by ἀθροώτερα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 348b10 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>neuter</i> as <i>adverb</i>, λάβρον ἐπαιγίζων.. Ἔρως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 5.285.2 (Paul. Sil.). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> after [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], of men, <b>boisterous, turbulent</b>, especiallyin talking, <b>hasty</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 634; λάβροι παγγλωσσίᾳ 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 2.86; λ. στόμα 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 177, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1147; λ. ὄμμα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 379 (_anapaest meter_, assuming variant). \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>fierce</b>, δράκοντος λαβρόταται γένυες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.244, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 253 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>violent, impetuous</b>, λ. πρὸς τὴν ἐπιθυμίαν τὴν τῆς τροφῆς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 717a23 (_comparative_)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; λάβρῳ χρώμενοι τῷ ποτῷ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 5.26; λάβρος εἰς Βάκχον ὀλισθών “Anthologia Graeca” 11.25 (1st c.AD: Apollonides Epigrammaticus); λαγνεῖαι λαβρόταται 5th-4th c.BC: Timaeus Locrus Philosophus 103a; ἐπιθυμία 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 717a28; Ἔρως “Anthologia Graeca” 5.267 (Paul. Sil.); λάβρῳ μαχαίρᾳ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 403. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>adverb</i> λάβρως <b>violently, furiously</b>, [ἵπποι] ἄνακτα φέρουσι λάβρως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 988 (compare λαβροπόδης, -συτος); λ. ὕει 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 4.7.1; ἄνεμοι καταιγίζοντες λ. 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 5.26; ἀθρόως καὶ λ. 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Ἰβηρική” 18, compare “Hann.” 48; διδόναι [τὸ ὀξύμελι] κατ᾽ ὀλίγον καὶ μὴ λ. 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ διαίτης ὀξέων” 58, compare 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.452. \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>eagerly, greedily</b>, λ. διαρταμᾶν (of the eagle) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 1022 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τῇ βρώσει χρῆται λ. (of the lion) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 594b18, compare 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.71.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]—poetical word, used also in <i>Ionic dialect</i> and late Prose. [λᾱ- by position in <i>Epic dialect</i>: λᾰ- [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Or.” [same place], “HF” 861 (troch.), “Anthologia Graeca” 11.25 (1st c.AD: Apollonides Epigrammaticus).] \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8150","accentedUnicode":"λάβρος","shortDef":"fierce","mediumDef":"fierce","stepGloss":"fierce","stepTransliteration":"labros","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}